# Java Methods: A Comprehensive Guide

## Introduction

Methods in Java are fundamental building blocks of object-oriented programming that allow you to organize and reuse code effectively.

## Concept Overview

A method is a block of code that performs a specific task and can be called multiple times throughout a program. Methods help break down complex problems into smaller, manageable pieces.

## Syntax

```java
// Basic method declaration
public void sayHello() {
    System.out.println("Hello, World!");
}

// Method with parameters
public int addNumbers(int a, int b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Method with return type
public String getGreeting(String name) {
    return "Welcome, " + name + "!";
}
```

## Key Points

- Methods must be declared within a class
- Methods can have return types (void, int, String, etc.)
- Parameters are optional but often used
- Methods can be public, private, or have other access modifiers
- Use camelCase for method names

## Common Mistakes

- Forgetting to declare a return type
- Not handling method parameters correctly
- Overlooking method visibility and access

